Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.89,0:00:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na glittering shooting star!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts dried by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.69,0:00:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's point is evidence-finding!\NDon't overlook anything important!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.95,0:00:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.65,0:00:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.62,0:00:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Hobo Artist Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:01:59.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Art Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:04.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Abstract Art of the World
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was nice of my client to give\Nme free passes for solving his case,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.24,0:02:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but these make no sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.53,0:02:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but they're still pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree with you, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.38,0:02:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that guy up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, sir! Don't touch the art!\NAnd smoking is prohibited!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.56,0:02:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a weirdo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.77,0:02:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Here goes!\NCatch it, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.73,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we playing baseball\Nand not soccer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan! It's all yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you aiming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?! I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Didn't I see you at the...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.26,0:03:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were drawing sketches?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He was drawing these just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.98,0:03:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you always\Ndraw the same pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why... do I always...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.78,0:03:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.03,0:03:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan. Is he hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we call an ambulance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who... who am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.21,0:03:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even remember my name...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.50,0:04:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he have amnesia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! The ball hit his arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My head hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My head... my head hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.81,0:04:17.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamada General Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, he really has amnesia?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His headaches occur\Nas his memory slowly returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.99,0:04:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, he still doesn't\Nknow who he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.00,0:04:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! We notified the police,\Nso we'll know soon enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops! I forgot to\Nleave his sketchbook!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:05:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that man's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two, check the emergency exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.37,0:05:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the patient you\Nbrought in just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it he didn't leave\Nthrough the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.21,0:05:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we haven't seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about his clothes and things?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.38,0:05:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he changed clothes\Nand took his things with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did his memory return?!\NBut then why would he disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.85,0:05:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?! Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.73,0:05:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! Why aren't we playing soccer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.99,0:05:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}! It's yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.95,0:05:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it! It's all mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:05:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay, Genta?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.00,0:06:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the man from yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the ball hit him again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was strangled with\Nstring or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.60,0:06:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was murdered?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, he was strangled to death,\Nprobably sometime last evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His pockets are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big idea?! Bugging\Nthe inspector again, are ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NThese children discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.63,0:06:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was here last night, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.13,0:06:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps the killer marked him\Nand mugged him when he was alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A robbery, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:07:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Inspector! The victim's\Npaint supplies are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paint supplies?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His canvas and easel are gone, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So is his paint box!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His bag, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had such items?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must've been stolen as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right! Nobody'd ever steal\Nthat junk, it'd just weigh 'em down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, one of his\Nshoelaces is in a granny knot,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which means he didn't tie it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.51,0:07:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ginkgo leaf in his shoe\Nis strange, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no ginkgo trees here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from his location,\Nhe must've been killed somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tossed over the bridge\Nduring the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why did he disappear\Nfrom the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't seem like\Nany ordinary mugging to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to find out who he is first...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.57,0:07:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Inspector, I think this is actually--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I'll tolerate you getting\Nin my way, but not the Inspector's!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.13,0:08:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go play somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.04,0:08:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, Inspector.\NLet's have a look at the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's get started!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.84,0:08:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the Junior Detective League!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Talk about dependable!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:21.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Department Store
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, behind the house is a pylon\Non the right and a factory on the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we just find that house!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.79,0:08:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here, either!\NHow about you, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:08:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!\NIt even has a ginkgo tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:02.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Okita House Cleaning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hayase..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This car's brand new.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does she want it so clean\Nthat there's not a single hair left?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same with the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.57,0:09:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wants everything a\Nperson might touch wiped clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it's\Nto erase fingerprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What're you guys doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:33.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hayase Kimie (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's still dirty. Go through again and-- oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.05,0:09:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! I have some nice\Ncookies! Just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her apron's tied with a granny knot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sofas and tables are\Ndifferent, and there's no tv.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's completely different\Nfrom the pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:10:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Miss. Did you\Nremodel this room recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.70,0:10:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's all the old stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I threw it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that painting new, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.79,0:10:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It arrived from the art gallery\Njust two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it lovely?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.76,0:10:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad. It'll be hard to prove, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally,\Nwhat did you want to ask me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, you go, Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.10,0:10:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:39.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hayase Tatsuo (47)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lt looks just like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even that characteristic nose\Nis the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He's wearing glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did he pass away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.16,0:10:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks just like a murder\Nvictim discovered this morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.21,0:10:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was someone else.\NMy husband supposedly died a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.84,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:10:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disaster disappearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.59,0:11:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A person is normally presumed\Ndead after going missing for seven years,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but people in natural\Ndisasters or shipwrecks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.51,0:11:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are presumed dead after only one year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.14,0:11:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, a rich\Nbanker by the name of Hayase
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was caught in an avalanche\Nand went missing a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.03,0:11:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a good memory, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm such a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, there were rumors that\Nhe embezzled huge sums of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was just about to be investigated,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the authorities figured\Nit was a sham at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.01,0:11:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The embezzled money\Ncouldn't be tracked down,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.22,0:11:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it was assumed\Nhe disappeared with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, it was eventually called\Na disaster disappearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.14,0:11:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Conan. Have you\Ntold Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! He had her verify the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:06.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,District Police Station - Charnel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He resembles my husband, but it's not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, does the late Hayase-{\i1}san\N{\i0}have any relatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A father, or mother, or siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He had no relatives.\NWhy do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you're the\Nonly one who can verify his body?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.47,0:12:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.47,0:12:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally,\Ndid Mr. Hayase do paintings?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We can check the\Nfingerprints on his old things!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.36,0:12:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Inspector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband did indeed paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was painting in the mountains\Nwhen the avalanche struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I threw out all his things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The media and society\Nstarted to condemn me, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the whole embezzlement thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to forget my husband quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.55,0:13:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, all we can\Ndo is take her word for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There's no doubt that\Nthe victim is Hayase Tatsuo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.90,0:13:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be\Nsome way to prove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.03,0:13:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! We left\Nsomething here last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those cookies earlier were so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd love to have more!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that what you "left" here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.92,0:13:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.71,0:13:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.97,0:13:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any traces\Nleft that the victim was here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.97,0:13:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some kind of burn mark...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:13:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ginkgo leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.98,0:14:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're lying here, then they'd\Ncome inside if the window was open...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.98,0:14:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! The leaf,\Nthe window, the burn mark,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the glasses-less victim,\Nand the painting on the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've finally found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Proof that Hayase-{\i1}san\N{\i0}returned here with his memory intact!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.84,0:14:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure! The victim is\Nunquestionably Hayase Tatsuo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've finally found proof of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.39,0:14:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Really, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, Inspector Megure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Come immediately, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what is this all about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel.\NMori-{\i1}kun {\i0}will explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.03,0:14:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought you were going to--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.37,0:15:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.79,0:15:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to shed light on\Nthe truth behind this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.17,0:15:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One year ago, Mr. Hayase went\Ninto the mountains to paint
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.47,0:15:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was caught in an avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He luckily survived,\Nbut lost his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then walked all over\Nas a wandering artist,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unconsciously drawing\Nhis house all the while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A year passed, and he was judged\Nto have disappeared by disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, his wife inherited his estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you couldn't\Nhave him showing up now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.30,0:15:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her inheritance likely included\Nthe missing money he had embezzled!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:16:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, she killed Mr. Hayase when\Nhe returned yesterday, memory intact!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she could keep all the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.57,0:16:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband died in\Nthe mountains a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you have proof he was alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.03,0:16:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, I don't. That's because\Nyou disposed of all of his things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, you removed all\Npossible fingerprints and hairs, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even hired a cleaning\Ncompany to be extra sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means you can't prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the victim left behind\Na connection with you:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a gingko leaf in his shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no gingko\Ntrees where he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's a gingko tree next to\Nmy house... and all over Tokyo, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One other thing, for some reason,\Nonly one of the victim's shoelaces
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.95,0:17:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was in a granny knot...\Njust like your apron!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.62,0:17:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably, when you put his\Nshoes on after killing him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.34,0:17:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you noticed one was untied!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not wanting to be suspected,\Nyou decided to tie it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.52,0:17:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Claiming I did it because\Nof a granny knot? Hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have no more of these insults!\NI'll take you to court!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?\NYou have proof, I hope?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.45,0:17:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, let me\Nget to the real point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.53,0:17:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Stand in front of the painting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.04,0:17:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.96,0:17:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.42,0:17:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Miss. Was Mr. Hayase\Na heavy smoker?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you hate cigarettes, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No smoking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.40,0:18:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hayase, after regaining his\Nmemory and leaving the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stood in front of this painting,\Ncigarette in mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, you opened the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.16,0:18:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Several ginkgo leaves\Nlikely fell inside then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.67,0:18:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One got stuck to his foot\Nwhile he was inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.67,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do you know\Nhe was smoking there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.84,0:18:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the burn mark\Non the wooden cabinet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.60,0:18:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As there was no ashtray in\Nthe house, he put it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.44,0:18:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're not going to make\Nme laugh by saying that's your proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.28,0:19:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, was Mr. Hayase near-sighted?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.95,0:19:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that painting the way\Nhe did at the Beika Art Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he got near it and--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.93,0:19:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! His fingerprints, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fingerprints? Are you saying\Nthere are some on that painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.27,0:19:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you said she cleaned the\Nwhole place of fingerprints and hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She even hired a cleaning company.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But think about it, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.87,0:19:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No professional would\Nwipe down a bare painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if he had a habit of grabbing\Npaintings, she would've known!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.50,0:20:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. That habit began\Nafter he lost his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before he got amnesia, Mr. Hayase\Nwore glasses for his near-sightedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he lost them in the avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, he started getting close\Nto paintings because of his poor vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he formed a habit of\Ngrabbing them to get a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Mr. Hayase returned here\Nand looked at the painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.37,0:20:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his wife likely opened the\Nwindow to air out the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As her back was to him,\Nshe probably didn't notice this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.17,0:20:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, she overlooked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.17,0:20:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss. Can you explain why\Nyour husband's fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.13,0:20:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are on a picture you\Nput up two days ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Call the examiners!\NCheck for prints!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I concede.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.52,0:21:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did come here.\NIt's all as the detective said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed him. I drugged his coffee\Nand strangled him with a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, why did you dump him\Nin such a conspicuous spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to wait any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was finally classified as missing\Nand I got his embezzled money!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If people learned he\Nwas alive, amnesia or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.05,0:21:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he might've lost all his money!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.93,0:21:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously! I suffered because\Nmy husband was an embezzler...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.35,0:21:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That money was mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to get my time,\Nand life, back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.94,0:21:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have plenty of time.\NBehind bars, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.50,0:23:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another great nap!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.51,0:23:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Dad! You even\Nsolved the missing-persons case!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should hire you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did someone go missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.77,0:23:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad feeling about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.64,0:23:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That lousy Shinichi'll never\Ncome back unless I look for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.56,0:23:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.02,0:23:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse! He'll ruin my\Nreputation if he comes back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope he stays missing forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:23:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the score, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.83,0:24:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina-{\i1}kun{\i0}? What're you doing?\NWhat's with that car?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.46,0:24:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Shiina-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\NSay something, will ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.29,0:24:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s been--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.47,0:24:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,kidnapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.22,0:24:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it! A kidnapping\Nright before my eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.26,0:24:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.69,0:24:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Popular Artist\NAbduction Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.11,0:24:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.47,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two-Mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode that popular group shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.90,0:24:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, what's your relationship with Two-Mix?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.96,0:24:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eep.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.66,0:24:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
